    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you have dementia (memory loss and thinking problems) caused by another medical condition, and your symptoms are mild but include agitation, restlessness, or irritability. Dementia in this category isn't from Alzheimer's disease but instead stems from conditions like Parkinson's disease, stroke, or other neurological problems. You may experience some confusion and difficulty with daily tasks, along with feelings of anxiety or behavioral changes.",
