    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you have mild dementia (significant memory loss and thinking problems) caused by another medical condition, and you're also experiencing mood changes like depression or anxiety. The dementia is in its early stages, but it's affecting your ability to remember things and think clearly, and these cognitive changes are accompanied by emotional symptoms that need attention. Your doctor has identified that another disease you have is causing both the memory loss and the mood disturbance, rather than these being separate or primary conditions.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, geriatricians, psychiatrists, and primary care physicians use this code when diagnosing dementia related to an underlying condition (such as Parkinson's disease, Lewy body disease, or other medical illnesses) with accompanying depression or mood symptoms. This code is commonly documented in neurology and memory care clinics, and may appear on EOB statements as part of a diagnosis for ongoing cognitive and psychiatric management.",
