    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means someone has severe dementia—a serious decline in memory, thinking, and daily functioning—without a specific identified cause, and they are also experiencing significant agitation or restlessness. Agitation in dementia can include irritability, pacing, verbal outbursts, or aggressive behavior that makes care more challenging. This code indicates the person needs substantial support and supervision for safety and activities of daily living.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, geriatricians, psychiatrists, and primary care physicians use this code when documenting advanced dementia with behavioral disturbances in hospital or long-term care settings. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients in memory care facilities or those receiving intensive behavioral management alongside dementia treatment.",
