    "shortDesc": "Amnestic disorder due to known physiological condition",
    "longDesc": "Amnestic disorder due to known physiological condition",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you have memory loss that is directly caused by a physical condition affecting your brain—such as a head injury, stroke, infection, vitamin deficiency, or other medical problem—rather than a psychiatric disorder. You may struggle to form new memories, recall recent events, or remember personal information, and doctors can identify the specific physical cause through testing. This is different from normal forgetfulness because it's significant enough to interfere with daily functioning and stems from an identifiable medical condition.",
