    "plainEnglish": "Catatonia is a state where someone becomes nearly unresponsive, with reduced movement and speech, or sometimes exhibits repetitive, purposeless movements—and in this case, it's caused by an underlying medical condition (like an infection, metabolic disorder, or medication side effect) rather than a psychiatric illness. When doctors identify a physical cause for the catatonic symptoms, they use this code to indicate that treating the underlying medical problem is key to resolving the catatonia. A patient might experience being \"frozen\" or unresponsive, difficulty moving or speaking, or unusual repetitive behaviors that improve once the underlying medical condition is treated.",
