    "plainEnglish": "This code describes anxiety symptoms that are directly caused by an underlying medical condition rather than a primary anxiety disorder. For example, an overactive thyroid, heart problems, or certain medications can trigger persistent worry, nervousness, or panic attacks; when a doctor identifies that specific medical condition as the source of your anxiety, they use this code to document that connection. This is important because treating the underlying medical problem often improves or resolves the anxiety symptoms.",
