    "plainEnglish": "Postconcussional syndrome is a collection of symptoms that develop after a concussion or mild traumatic brain injury and can last for weeks or months. Patients may experience persistent headaches, dizziness, difficulty concentrating, memory problems, irritability, sleep disturbances, and sensitivity to light or noise—even after they've physically recovered from the initial injury. These symptoms occur without major structural damage to the brain and can significantly affect daily activities like work, school, and social interactions.",
