    "shortDesc": "Alcohol abuse, in remission",
    "longDesc": "Alcohol abuse, in remission",
    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates that you have a history of alcohol abuse, but you are currently in remission—meaning you are not actively abusing alcohol right now. Remission doesn't necessarily mean you've quit completely; it means your alcohol use is controlled and you're no longer meeting the criteria for active alcohol abuse (excessive drinking that causes harm to your health, relationships, or responsibilities). Your doctor is documenting this status to track your recovery and ensure you receive appropriate monitoring and support.",
    "whoUses": "Addiction medicine specialists, psychiatrists, primary care physicians, and substance abuse treatment providers use this code when patients are in recovery from alcohol abuse. It commonly appears on EOBs when documenting ongoing outpatient counseling, follow-up care, or rehabilitation services, and may also be used during mental health or general medical visits where alcohol history is relevant to treatment.",
