    "whoUses": "This code is most commonly used by emergency medicine physicians, primary care doctors, and addiction medicine specialists in urgent care or hospital settings when treating acutely intoxicated patients. It rarely appears on patient EOB statements since it's primarily a clinical documentation code used internally by healthcare providers rather than a billable diagnosis on insurance claims.",
