    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates that a person has been using alcohol in an unspecified pattern and is now experiencing withdrawal symptoms, but without serious complications like seizures or delirium. Alcohol withdrawal happens when someone who has been drinking heavily stops or significantly reduces their alcohol intake, causing their body to react with uncomfortable symptoms such as shaking, sweating, anxiety, or nausea. The 'uncomplicated' part means these withdrawal symptoms are present but not severe enough to threaten life or require emergency intervention.",
