    "rawCode": "F11121",
    "shortDesc": "Opioid abuse with intoxication delirium",
    "longDesc": "Opioid abuse with intoxication delirium",
    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates that a person is misusing opioid medications or drugs (like heroin, prescription painkillers, or fentanyl) and has experienced delirium—a serious state of confusion, disorientation, and altered thinking—as a direct result of being intoxicated by those opioids. Delirium from opioid intoxication is different from typical drug 'high'; it involves dangerous confusion, hallucinations, and difficulty thinking clearly that requires medical attention.",
    "whoUses": "Addiction medicine specialists, emergency medicine doctors, psychiatrists, and hospital-based providers use this code when treating patients in acute opioid intoxication with severe mental confusion. It commonly appears in emergency department and inpatient psychiatric records, and may show on EOBs when patients receive emergency or crisis care for opioid-related complications.",
