    "shortDesc": "Opioid abuse with opioid-induced mood disorder",
    "longDesc": "Opioid abuse with opioid-induced mood disorder",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you are struggling with opioid abuse (using opioids in a harmful way without medical supervision or beyond prescribed amounts) and, as a direct result of that opioid use, you are experiencing a mood disorder—such as depression or anxiety. Opioids can alter your brain chemistry and emotional regulation, so when someone misuses these drugs, they often develop mood problems that are caused by the opioid use itself rather than by an underlying mental health condition alone.",
