    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a situation where someone is misusing opioids (prescription painkillers or street drugs like heroin) and as a direct result of that opioid use, they're experiencing sexual dysfunction—meaning difficulty with sexual arousal, performance, or satisfaction. Opioids can interfere with hormones and nerve signals that control sexual function, so this is a recognized medical consequence of opioid misuse rather than a separate condition.",
    "whoUses": "This code is used by addiction medicine specialists, psychiatrists, primary care physicians, and pain management doctors when treating patients who abuse opioids and report sexual side effects. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients in substance use disorder treatment programs or those receiving concurrent treatment for both opioid misuse and sexual dysfunction.",
