    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a situation where someone has developed a physical and psychological dependence on opioids (narcotic pain medications or heroin) AND is experiencing sexual dysfunction as a direct result of that opioid use. Opioids can interfere with the body's ability to produce sex hormones and affect nerve function related to sexual response, leading to difficulties with arousal, performance, or satisfaction. This diagnosis recognizes that the sexual problem is specifically tied to the opioid dependence, not caused by something else.",
