    "shortDesc": "Cannabis abuse with unspecified cannabis-induced disorder",
    "longDesc": "Cannabis abuse with unspecified cannabis-induced disorder",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis indicates that you have a pattern of cannabis (marijuana) use that's causing problems in your life, along with some type of mental health or physical condition related to the cannabis use, but the specific condition hasn't been identified yet. Cannabis abuse means you're using marijuana in a way that's harmful—such as using it despite knowing it's causing issues at work, school, relationships, or with your health—rather than being dependent on it. The 'unspecified' part means your doctor has documented that cannabis is causing you some kind of disorder or complication, but they haven't yet pinpointed exactly what that is (it could be anxiety, depression, sleep problems, or another condition).",
    "whoUses": "Psychiatrists, addiction medicine specialists, primary care physicians, and substance abuse counselors use this code when treating patients with problematic cannabis use patterns. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients seen in mental health clinics, addiction treatment programs, or primary care visits where cannabis use is being addressed clinically.",
