    "shortDesc": "Cannabis dependence with psychotic disorder with delusions",
    "longDesc": "Cannabis dependence with psychotic disorder with delusions",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you have both a cannabis (marijuana) addiction and a mental health condition involving delusions—false beliefs that feel real to you but aren't based in reality. The cannabis use is connected to triggering or worsening these delusions, which could involve believing things that aren't true or feeling that others are plotting against you. This is a serious condition that typically requires treatment for both the substance dependence and the psychiatric symptoms.",
    "whoUses": "Psychiatrists, addiction medicine specialists, and substance abuse counselors use this code when treating patients with co-occurring cannabis dependence and psychotic symptoms. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients receiving inpatient psychiatric treatment, medication management, or intensive outpatient programs that address both conditions.",
