    "shortDesc": "Cannabis dependence with psychotic disorder, unspecified",
    "longDesc": "Cannabis dependence with psychotic disorder, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you have a physical and psychological dependence on cannabis (marijuana) and you're also experiencing psychotic symptoms, though the specific type of psychotic disorder hasn't been specified. Psychotic symptoms can include hallucinations (seeing or hearing things that aren't there), delusions (false beliefs), or a disconnection from reality. Cannabis dependence combined with psychosis can create a serious situation where your mind struggles to distinguish between what's real and what isn't, and you may have difficulty controlling your cannabis use despite these mental health problems.",
    "whoUses": "Psychiatrists, addiction medicine specialists, and mental health professionals use this code when treating patients with co-occurring cannabis use disorder and psychotic symptoms. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients receiving inpatient psychiatric treatment, emergency department visits for acute psychotic episodes, or outpatient mental health and addiction counseling services.",
