    "shortDesc": "Cannabis dependence with cannabis-induced anxiety disorder",
    "longDesc": "Cannabis dependence with cannabis-induced anxiety disorder",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you have a physical and psychological dependence on cannabis (marijuana) and are also experiencing an anxiety disorder that has been caused or worsened by your cannabis use. Cannabis dependence develops when regular use leads to tolerance (needing more to get the same effect) and withdrawal symptoms when you stop, while the anxiety disorder—characterized by excessive worry, panic, or nervousness—is directly tied to the effects of cannabis on your brain chemistry.",
    "whoUses": "Psychiatrists, addiction medicine specialists, and mental health counselors commonly use this code when treating patients with substance use disorders and co-occurring psychiatric conditions. It frequently appears on EOB statements for patients receiving treatment at addiction clinics, psychiatric facilities, or mental health practices, as it documents both the primary substance use disorder and its associated mental health complication for insurance purposes.",
