    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates that someone has developed a dependence on cannabis (marijuana) and is experiencing some kind of cannabis-related mental health or medical problem, but the specific problem hasn't been clearly identified or documented yet. Cannabis dependence means the person has developed a pattern of regular use where they feel unable to function normally without it, and they may experience withdrawal symptoms when they try to stop. The 'unspecified' part means the doctor knows cannabis is causing additional health issues beyond just the dependence itself, but those issues need further clarification or evaluation.",
