    "shortDesc": "Bipolar disorder, unspecified",
    "longDesc": "Bipolar disorder, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "Bipolar disorder is a mental health condition where a person experiences extreme mood swings that alternate between periods of very high energy and euphoria (called manic episodes) and periods of deep sadness and depression. These mood shifts can last for days or weeks and significantly affect a person's ability to work, sleep, and maintain relationships. The exact cause isn't fully understood, but it involves a combination of genetics, brain chemistry, and life stressors.",
    "whoUses": "Psychiatrists, psychologists, primary care physicians, and mental health counselors use this code to diagnose and treat patients with bipolar disorder. It commonly appears on insurance EOB statements for mental health visits, psychiatric medications, and therapy sessions, and is often used in outpatient mental health clinics and psychiatric hospitals.",
