    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis describes a person experiencing their first significant period of depression that is relatively mild in severity. During this episode, someone might feel persistently sad, lose interest in activities they normally enjoy, have trouble sleeping, or experience low energy and difficulty concentrating—but these symptoms aren't so severe that they prevent them from functioning in daily life. The key distinction is that this is the first time they're experiencing a major depressive episode, and the symptoms, while troubling, aren't at the most severe level.",
