    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a person experiencing a first episode of clinical depression—a serious mood disorder where someone feels persistently sad, hopeless, or loses interest in activities they normally enjoy. The depression is severe enough to affect their daily functioning, work, relationships, or sleep, and doctors cannot yet determine the specific severity level or whether it's mild, moderate, or severe.",
